// Detection 2: Business Email Compromise - Post-Compromise Actions
//
// What it finds:
//   The control-plane actions the attacker took right after taking over the
//   dmorris account: a malicious inbox rule that hides invoice/payment/wire
//   emails (moves them to RSS Feeds and marks them read), and external mail
//   forwarding to an attacker address (attacker-collect@proton.me). Both from
//   the same IP as the sign-in attack (102.89.34.180).
//
// Why it matters:
//   This is the goal of a BEC: intercept and steal financial email without the
//   real user noticing. The inbox rule hides it; the forwarding exfiltrates it.
//   Correlating these AuditLogs actions with Detection 1's sign-in compromise
//   ties the whole incident together.
//
// MITRE ATT&CK:
//   T1564.008 Email Hiding Rules, T1114.003 Email Forwarding Rule

AuditLogs_CL
| where UserPrincipalName == "dmorris@contoso.com"
| project TimeGenerated, OperationName, InitiatedByIP, TargetResource, ModifiedProperties
| sort by TimeGenerated asc
